                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.01 Foreign Control/741a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Liberia (<persName type="to">Werlich</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-11T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 11, 1933—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>62. We have received reports that the Liberian Legislature is about to adjourn.
                    Please telegraph briefly the present situation with regard to the consideration
                    of the League Plan and your suggestions as to what, if anything further, should
                    be done to secure its adoption. Have your colleagues exerted any pressure in its
                    favor?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
